   <refnamediv>
       <refname>growthr </refname>
               <refpurpose>growth rate of a ts </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>ts=growthr(ts,lag)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> ts </term> =     a timeseries</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> lag </term> =     an integer (optional, set to 1 if not provided)</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> ts </term> =     the growthr of the time series</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Computes ts(t)/ts(t-lag)-1. If a value for ts is 0, then the corresponding value is set to 'NA'.
 
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
load(GROCERDIR+'\data\pigiron.dat')
gx = growthr(prigiron)
// growth rate of the monthly series pigiron used for the Bry-Bosachna demo
ga = growthr(x,12)
// year on year growth rate of the monthly series pigiron.
 
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>AUTHOR</title>
Eric Dubois 2002
        </refsection>
</refentry>
